Jane=E2=80=99s Addiction

Does the 51-year-old Jane really want to step into the newly vacant executi=
ve chairperson role after knifing her cousin? My understanding is that some=
 executives and family members believe a more visible role for Jane would h=
elp the family retain control. =E2=80=9CThe idea is that if Jane can replac=
e William, she=E2=80=99ll have more power and can act as St=C3=A9phane=E2=
=80=99s boss to better manage steering the ship,=E2=80=9D said a source fam=
iliar with the company. A person close to the family disagreed. =E2=80=9CJa=
ne was hoping she would get C.E.O., and since she didn=E2=80=99t, she wants=
 to go in and just be a board member where she can add value,=E2=80=9D this=
 person affirmed to me. However, said a person familiar with the situation:=
 =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t think this is over. I don=E2=80=99t think Jane go=
es from that career to attending four board meetings a year.=E2=80=9D

Either way, I=E2=80=99m hearing
that some senior-level employees are very eager for January, when de La Fav=
erie officially starts in his new role. =E2=80=9CThe last couple of years, =
the focus on Who=E2=80=99s next? or What=E2=80=99s next? has been such a di=
straction for everyone, and this other drama that=E2=80=99s unfolding is ye=
t another distraction,=E2=80=9D said a current Lauder executive. =E2=80=9CE=
veryone is over this and ready to move forward. We want to do the things we=
 need to do to reposition this company. There are finally real changes comi=
ng.=E2=80=9D

That=E2=80=99s it from Rachel and me. By the way, I=E2=80=99ve been invited=
 to two tarot card readings, sponsored by fashion brands, within the past 2=
4 hours. I don=E2=80=99t know what it means, but it means something.

